Language name: SONGHAI
Language number: 4200
Alternate names: 
Classification: Nilo-Saharan, Songhai
Comments: Prost description of vowels suggests the 
possibility of a larger number of mid vowels.  Nasalized 
vowels occur without an adjoining nasal consonant only in 
a few uncommon words.
Sources: 

Prost, A. 1956. La Langue Songay et ses Dialectes 
(Memoires de l'Institut francais d'Afrique Noire 47). 
IFAN, Dakar.

Williamson, K. 1967. Songhai Word List (Gao Dialect). 
Research Notes, Department of Linguistics and Nigerian 
Languages, University of Ibadan, 1/3: 1-34.